# Considering that we are in the current directory

## Pull image

```bash
docker pull abarchibody/sign-in-up
```

## Build image
```bash
docker build -t sign-in-up .
``` 
### -t: the target is the name of the image,
### we will refere it when run it the container

## Tag image

```bash
docker pull abarchibody/sign-in-up sign-in-up
```

## Push image

```bash
docker push abarchibody/sign-in-up
```

## Run container
```bash 
docker run -p 80:80 sign-in-up
# or
docker run -p 80:80 abarchibody/sign-in-up
```
### -d: detachable mode
### -p: port mapping
### --name: the name of the container
### at last i specified the image name to run the container